<subSubSection id="C3266556D364FFC3FF17FCB2DF8CFBFD" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8336DDD364FFC3FF17FCB2DF8CFBFD" blockId="7.[151,1437,541,1432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD364FFC3FF17FCB2DFF5FC8D" bold="true" box="[199,442,865,891]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Diagnosis of female.</emphasis>
Compared to male (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B2CD364FFC3FD76FCB2DD96FC8A" author="Bayarsaikhan, U. &amp; Bae, Y. S." box="[678,985,865,892]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" pagination="241 - 252" refId="ref6065" refString="Bayarsaikhan, U. &amp; Bae, Y. S. (2015) Three new species of Stictane Hampson, 1900 (Erebidae, Arctiinae) from Cambodia, with checklist of Stictane. Zootaxa, 3981 (2), 241 - 252. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3981.2.5" type="journal article" year="2015">Bayarsaikhan &amp; Bae 2015</bibRefCitation>
: fig 1; present paper: 7a), the female is slightly larger in size (length of forewing 
<quantity id="4CC49B38D364FFC3FDBEFC56DCE0FC69" box="[622,687,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
in male (
<typeStatus id="5487887FD364FFC3FCC9FC56DDCEFC56" box="[793,897,901,928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">holotype</typeStatus>
), 
<quantity id="4CC49B38D364FFC3FC44FC56DD99FC69" box="[916,982,901,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
in female, 
<figureCitation id="13072A58D364FFC3FB85FC56DAEEFC56" box="[1109,1185,901,928]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,191,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[163,1424,181,1787]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. General view of the body of adults of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 2. S. fractilinea, female (INU˗10364T). 3. S. gemina, male (INU˗10356T). 4. S. mlcochi, male (INU˗10355T). 5a. S. pectenicorniculum, male (OPU˗009T). 5b. ditto, female (OPU˗008T). 6a. S. fuscus, male (OPU˗001T). 6b. ditto, female (OPU˗017T). 7a. S. cambodiensis, male (INU˗10358T). 7b. ditto, female (INU˗10362T). 8a. S. bokorensis, male (OPU˗014T). 8b. ditto, female (OPU˗018M). 9. S. kualabohi, female (INU˗10351T). 10. S. transversana, male (OPU˗015T). 11a. S. trigonica sp. n., male (holotype, INU˗10363T). 11b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗10353T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571783/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Fig 7b</figureCitation>
). The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D5ED364FFC3FF66FC7ADF2CFC35" authorityName="Bayarsaikhan &amp; Bae" authorityYear="2015" box="[182,355,937,963]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Stictane" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cambodensis">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD364FFC3FF66FC7ADF2CFC35" box="[182,355,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">S. cambodensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13072A58D364FFC3FEA2FC7ADFF2FC32" box="[370,445,937,964]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1374,1398]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,195,1336]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1436,181,1350]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. Female genitalia of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 20. S. fractilinea (INU˗10364T). 21. S. pectenicorniculum (OPU˗008T). 22. S. fuscus (OPU˗011T). 23. S. bokorensis (OPU˗018Malaysia). 24. S. trigonica sp. n. (paratype, INU˗10353T). 25. S. kualabohi (INU˗10351T). 26. S. cambodiensis (INU˗10362T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571787/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Fig 26</figureCitation>
) differ from other members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D5ED364FFC3FCCCFC7ADD39FC35" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1900" box="[796,886,937,963]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Stictane" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD364FFC3FCCCFC7ADD39FC35" box="[796,886,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Stictane</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dilated appendix bursae membranous and irregularly rectangular corpus bursae with strongly sclerotized proximal angle and diverse sized spines located widely in cervix of bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266556D364FFC3FF17FBC6DCEAFADD" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8336DDD364FFC3FF17FBC6DCEAFADD" blockId="7.[151,1437,541,1432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD364FFC3FF17FBC6DF82FBD9" bold="true" box="[199,461,1045,1071]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Description of female.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EACFD364FFC3FE03FBC6DC5FFBD9" box="[467,528,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13072A58D364FFC3FDCFFBC6DC24FBC6" box="[543,619,1045,1072]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,191,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[163,1424,181,1787]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. General view of the body of adults of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 2. S. fractilinea, female (INU˗10364T). 3. S. gemina, male (INU˗10356T). 4. S. mlcochi, male (INU˗10355T). 5a. S. pectenicorniculum, male (OPU˗009T). 5b. ditto, female (OPU˗008T). 6a. S. fuscus, male (OPU˗001T). 6b. ditto, female (OPU˗017T). 7a. S. cambodiensis, male (INU˗10358T). 7b. ditto, female (INU˗10362T). 8a. S. bokorensis, male (OPU˗014T). 8b. ditto, female (OPU˗018M). 9. S. kualabohi, female (INU˗10351T). 10. S. transversana, male (OPU˗015T). 11a. S. trigonica sp. n., male (holotype, INU˗10363T). 11b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗10353T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571783/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Fig 7b</figureCitation>
). Length of forewing 
<quantity id="4CC49B38D364FFC3FCB0FBC6DDEBFBD9" box="[864,932,1045,1071]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
. Head pale gray; frons and labial palpus dark brown. Thorax dark brown. Ground color of forewing pale gray; antemedian series of dark three spots distinct; straight medial dark band broad, rectangular at costal area; a distinct discoidal dot dark; postdiscal series of small dark spots curved outward. Upper apical patches fuscous. Hindwing dark gray. 
<emphasis id="B948EACFD364FFC3FBC3FB52DA9DFB6D" box="[1043,1234,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13072A58D364FFC3FB30FB52DB61FB6A" box="[1248,1326,1153,1180]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1374,1398]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,195,1336]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1436,181,1350]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. Female genitalia of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 20. S. fractilinea (INU˗10364T). 21. S. pectenicorniculum (OPU˗008T). 22. S. fuscus (OPU˗011T). 23. S. bokorensis (OPU˗018Malaysia). 24. S. trigonica sp. n. (paratype, INU˗10353T). 25. S. kualabohi (INU˗10351T). 26. S. cambodiensis (INU˗10362T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571787/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="488">Fig 26</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales weakly sclerotized, triangular. Apophyses posteriores two times longer than apophyses anteriores, both slender. Ostium rounded, membranous. Ductus bursae stout, tubular, sclerotized. Corpus bursae irregularly rectangular, weakly sclerotized, with strongly sclerotized proximal angle and diverse sized spines located widely in cervix of bursae. Appendix bursae membranous, dilated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266556D364FFC3FF17FAE6DDDCFAA6" box="[199,915,1333,1360]" pageId="7" pageNumber="488" type="distribution">
